CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 4, 1964, pg. 20 reads: "Masonic Gift - The membership of Most Worshipful Hiram Grand Lodge, Ancient Free and Accepted Masons, and Arabic Temple of the Order of the Mystic Shrine, AP&AM, of Pennsylvania, recently gave a $300 gift to Children's Hospital.  Shown above are (left to right) Luther Rice, Most Worshipful Grand Master, Hiram Grand Lodge; nurses Ophelia Dickerson, Margaret Michele, Catherine Tarter; Herbert Townes, Imperial Potentate; Lavonne Jeffreys, Alfred T. Hill, Potentate of Arabic Temple I, and hospital patients Michael, Cal and Laurette. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Shriners presenting donations to group of nurses, from left: Shriner Luther Rice, nurses Ophelia Dickerson, Margaret Michele, and Catherine Tarter, Shriner Herbert Townes, Lavonne Jeffreys, and Shriner Alfred T. Hill, posed with patients Michael, Cal, and Laurette in Children's Hospital of Pittsburgh, another version
